column8: Experium Science Academy exists to provide children from kindergarten through high school the opportunity to engage their minds and stretch their horizons through hands-on, lab-based science activities. We use inquiry-based learning techniques, instructed by true scientists, within a modern science laboratory dedicated to advancing children’s education.

ThoughtSTEM was founded by 3 UCSD PhD Students in October of 2012. What started as tutoring business with 5 students has swiftly grown into a county-wide service that has brought students starting at age 6 together throughout San Diego to explore, learn, and have fun!

The College of Engineering’s mission is “to educate students for careers of service, leadership and distinction in engineering or other fields by using a Learn by Doing, hands-on approach." As one of the college’s outreach programs, EPIC summer camp endeavors to extend this mission to grades 7-12.

Engineering Innovation is an exciting college-level summer program for motivated high school students with an aptitude in math and science and an interest in (or curiosity about) engineering. Students learn to think and problem-solve like engineers and have the opportunity to earn Johns Hopkins University (JHU) credit.

We approach each week with traditional learning styles, play-based learning, student driven challenges, and hands-on projects. By the end we have covered our subject with every learning style, every creative outlet, and every opportunity to laugh. This is the Brainy Bunch way.

OUR CAMPS ARE UNIQUE PROGRAMS THAT EMBRACE FUN, INDIVIDUALITY AND PERSONAL GROWTH. WE ARE POWERED BY OUR CAMPERS’ DESIRES TO RECREATE, SOCIALIZE AND EXPERIENCE SOMETHING NEW. OUR COUNSELORS ARE THE MENTORS OF FUN AND THE GATEKEEPERS OF OUR CAMP CULTURE. MOREOVER, WE VALUE CREATING A COMMUNITY ANDBUILDING A CULTURE OF CREATIVITY, FRIENDSHIP, INCLUSION AND RESPECT THAT PERMEATES ALL THAT WE DO.

ivyGOAL’s individualized tutoring is the ultimate educational support any child can have. Not only is it the most effective way for your child to achieve subject mastery, it is surprisingly cost effective. The reason that ivyGOAL tutoring works so well is our ability to pinpoint the strengths and weaknesses of the student's current knowledge base, and then customize a learning plan especially for them. By focusing the student’s energies on specific areas, we can ensure students reach their academic goals, often in less time and at lower cost than through any other teaching method.

Serra's Summer Sports & Recreation Camp is an action-packed day camp for boys and girls ages 5-12. Recreation activities, arts and crafts, sports skills and Camp Olympics are all a part of this fun, energetic camp. Activities are designed to promote fitness while encouraging fun and the development of social skills. Campers are grouped by age. High school and college aged counselors and adult supervisors provide guidance and support, and make the camp experience a memorable one. Both morning and afternoon extended care is also available.

Follow The Child is a discovery of the outdoors, where students explore nature through both art and science. FTC offers outdoor programs throughout the Bay Area as week-long summer camps and as year long science field trips

Learn to Discover's passion is to bring high-quality technology education to students from pre-Kindergarten through and beyond beyond Grade 12. These students might be in public schools, private schools and/or homeschools. Our main focus areas are STEM (science, technology, engineering and math), design skills, and art, and may be expanded to other areas as demand and market research dictates.

Exciting explorations, delightful discoveries and wild wonders await your family this summer at Hands-On Science Camp at the California Science Center. We offer more than 30 courses, including popular parent-and-child classes that give families a chance to investigate science together. The Hands-On Science Camp staff consists of education professionals and working professionals in science fields. Your child will have a unique, fun and engaging summer!

An incredible seed bed of learning and discovery, the purpose of a children’s museum is to inspire children to learn and grow, equip parents and teachers, and to be a safe place where learners of all abilities can do so at their own pace and focus on topics of interest to them. This is often referred to as “Free Range Learning.” What makes us different from a school is our approach to informal education. We believe in giving our guests hands-on experiences that are relevant and inspiring. - See more at: http://www.kidspacemuseum.org/about/kidspace-mission#sthash.24Tbn9Yf.dpuf

Education is a top priority of Heal the Bay. Whether you visit our public, marine education center on a school field trip, attend a free evening lecture on a marine science related topic, send your budding young scientist to ourMicro Biologist classes or to our summer camp, you will leave the Santa Monica Pier Aquarium with a new sense of wonder and appreciation for the amazing marine life of the Santa Monica Bay.

The ROBOTICS Hands-on STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering & Math) Summer Camp Enrichment is the perfect activity for Boys and Girls in Grades 1 thru 6 to experience the design, creation and building of Robots, Robotic Vehicles & BattleBots with a focus on Math & Science applications using real life goals & objectives. For 12-Years ROBOTICS has offered the Kids in attendance unique Tasks, Challenges and Time-Trials with Individual, Team & Group situations in diversified Platforms including Obstacle Courses, Targets (Various Sizes), Mars Terrain Sectionals (similar to JPL’s Red Room) and other unique Curriculum using California & National Science Standards. The Daily Registration for Each 3-Hour Session includes Instruction by ROBOTICS & THINGS and the Lab (Materials) Fee. Kids who Register for ALL 5-Daily Sessions will also receive a Motorized ROBOTICS Kit and a Certificate of Completion
These camps emphasize active learning through age-appropriate experiments, hands-on activities, and problem-solving.

For the past few years FAM has partnered with SAM Academy to provide a unique experience for nearly 200 children ages 7 to 15 to explore the wonderful worlds of art, music, and science! Our students became Young Makers! This summer, through a partnership with Shine Youth Theatre, we will be adding theatre to the mix.

Kids College, part of the Community Education Department at San Joaquin Delta College in Stockton, has been providing learning opportunities for the youth in our service area for more than 20 years. This unique program offers children and teens academic and enrichment workshops on a college campus. Kids College workshops are designed to teach new and meaningful skills, develop new interests and hobbies, excite students about learning, and provide an opportunity for them to explore possible careers.

ASEP Learning Center in Corona, CA is the headquarters of the After-School Enrichment Programs offices. Offered here are Art, Cartooning, Science, and Spanish classes. Group and individual classes for each of these subjects are available for grades K-8th. Individual tutoring for all ages is also available.

Our goal is to excite children's curiosity about the vast world of science, then satisfy it through hands-on projects and experiements! We teach critical thinking and integrated learning, as they are the basics of scientific thought and theory. There's so much to explore: physics, chemistry, biology, paleontology and on...All experiments are kid safe and fully supervised.
Our goal is to enhance the experience of living in our community; to play an active role in helping it be a happier, healthier, and more fulfilling place to live.

College for Kids is a spring enrichment program for children between ages 8-14. We are committed to teaching new and meaningful skills as your children participate in classes such as art, dance, fitness, science, media, and more. The program serves parents and children alike by providing fun, safe and educational activities with the added benefit of introducing kids to the college environment. In our new College for Kids format, your children will be able to choose between fun and exciting classes that meet your schedule.

From our Emmy Award winning Shamu TV DVD series to the thousands of visitors who participate in our park’s educational programs each year, SeaWorld artfully combines education and entertainment in a way that connects people to the sea and sea life like no where else. Here you’ll find ways to help your children or students make the most of all SeaWorld has to offer.

AstroCamp boasts one of the premier science and adventure programs in California. 1-week campers will spend their mornings at some of our core, exciting programs, and then in the afternoon, our 10-14 year olds will get the chance to pick from a variety of activities and design their own adventure. All of AstroCamp’s activities are hands-on and designed for campers to gain new skills and experiences, all while enjoying time with friends and our professional staff.

Discover an adventure like no other during the Safari Park’s Summer Camp! There may be many types of summer camp for kids, but few will have campers interacting with rhinos and giraffes, meeting meerkats, getting up close to cheetahs, feeding okapis, and discovering African wonders the way the Safari Park’s will. This is hands-on, join-in, be-a-part-of-it fun!

This summer we will be offering the best camp experience ever for those students who register with Modesto Junior College. No matter the interest of the child, they will do activities, crafts, while learning.

column1: Rigatoni & Robots a division of Cali Kids Club
column8: What truly makes Rigatoni & Robots so unique is our ability to make learning fun. This commitment to a hands-on, interactive approach to teaching kids, has caught the eye of many of today’s leading manufacturers of children’s products. We are proud to announce our partnerships with LEGO®, Toysmith®, KNEX™, 4M®, Elenco®, Consumer Crafts™, and others…as we not only teach about engineering, robotics, sewing, and the like…we let you go home with the actual products available at the large retail stores as part of the class fee and/or memberships. Imagine all of this while being surrounded by a cool California-themed surf/skate/snowboarding décor…come join the fun!
